# GPO Baseline Deployment

## Overview

This module automates the creation and deployment of a baseline Group Policy Object (GPO) in an Active Directory environment.

It demonstrates how administrative policies can be consistently applied across systems using PowerShell.

---

## Key Features

* Creates or reuses a baseline GPO
* Configures basic security-related settings
* Applies account lockout thresholds
* Demonstrates system hardening (e.g., USB storage control)
* Links the GPO to a specified Organizational Unit (OU)

---

## Tech Stack

* Windows Server (Active Directory Domain Services)
* PowerShell
* GroupPolicy module

---

## Project Structure

```text
.
├── Invoke-GPOBaseline.ps1
└── README.md
```

---

## How It Works

The script:

1. Checks if the baseline GPO exists
2. Creates it if not present
3. Applies policy settings via registry configuration
4. Links the GPO to a target OU

---

## Usage


.\Invoke-GPOBaseline.ps1

Optional:

.\Invoke-GPOBaseline.ps1 -TargetOU "OU=IT,DC=corp,DC=local"


---

## Example Use Case

Simulates deploying a standardized security baseline across systems in an enterprise environment.

---

## Design Considerations

* Idempotent execution (safe to re-run)
* Simple baseline for demonstration purposes
* Extendable with additional policy settings

---

## Key Learnings

* Automating Group Policy management
* Linking policies to directory structure
* Translating security requirements into enforceable configurations

---

## Future Improvements

* Domain-level policy configuration (fine-grained password policies)
* More comprehensive security baselines
* Reporting on applied GPO settings
* Integration with compliance frameworks

---

## Disclaimer

This script is intended for lab and demonstration purposes and does not represent a complete enterprise security baseline.
